Adamawa State House of Assembly has approved Governor Ahmadu Fintiri’s request to appoint 40 special advisers. Fintiri had earlier sent a letter to the lawmakers, seeking approval to appoint 40 special advisers to assist him in running the affairs of government. At a plenary session presided over by the speaker, Aminu Iya Abbas, the lawmakers granted the governor’s request. The speaker directed the clerk to communicate the approval to the governor. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The assembly also advised Fintiri to slam a two weeks suspension on the council chairman of Numan Local Government Area, Nathaniel Taylor. The lawmakers said the suspension would give them time to investigate allegation in a petition against Taylor signed by 10 out of 11 councillors. Adamawa assembly approves 40 special advisors for Governor Fintiri BREAKING: Fintiri nominates Atiku's son as commissioner Bauchi Assembly resumes, approves gov’s 10 advisers